{"session_id":"svc-1781497845232089169","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-06-15T04:30:45.261170186Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"sonnet-4.6","sticky":{"key_present":true,"assignment":"not_applicable","bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"resolved_harness":"claude-tui","harness_source":"auto_route","resolved_model":"sonnet-4.6","work_dir":"/Users/erik/Projects/.ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-34ea2a74-20260615T043027-6dad3872","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead in an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the contract: every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Too big if any holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across ~5+ files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, use a split-first pass.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, children once more; reject third-level splits with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child (copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add` only for legitimate child-to-child or sibling/replacement edges; never the parent.\u0026#xA;3. Use `parent=\u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` metadata and wire `parent -\u0026gt; child`.\u0026#xA;4. Write `no_changes_rationale.txt` under the bead metadata `bundle` path with child IDs, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Decomposition alone is success. Don\u0026#39;t mix it with implementation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC to concrete evidence (test, file, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Run git/index mutations sequentially; don\u0026#39;t parallelize `git add`, `git commit`, or staging/commit commands.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- If `lefthook run pre-commit` depends on staged files, rerun it after staging the exact commit set. A `no-staged-files` run is not acceptance evidence.\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; subject ends with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- Current-bead lifecycle is orchestrator-owned. Do not run `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --claim`, `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --status \u0026lt;status\u0026gt;`, `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --unclaim`, or `ddx bead close \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;`. Step 0 allows `ddx bead create`, `ddx bead dep add` for child-to-child or sibling/replacement edges, and `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;`.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `no_changes_rationale.txt` under the bead metadata `bundle` path before exiting. No commit or rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The `no_changes_rationale.txt` file under the bead metadata `bundle` path must contain one of:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;cmd\u0026gt;` — repo cwd; exit 0 closes, nonzero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: open` + `reason: \u0026lt;retryable\u0026gt;` — open, smart retry.\u0026#xA;- `status: proposed` + `reason: \u0026lt;operator needed\u0026gt;` — operator lane.\u0026#xA;- `status: blocked` + `reason: \u0026lt;external blocker\u0026gt;` — blocked lane.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;No pseudo-statuses. Bare rationales and `status: needs_investigation` are rejected.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;For orchestrator decomposition, add `orchestrator_action: decompose` alongside `status: open`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Reports go under the bead metadata `bundle` path in `.ddx/executions/`. **Never write reports to `/tmp` or outside the repo**. Use a named in-repo path when given; otherwise write `\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md` there. Commit it with the code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Mode and overrides\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_MODE=bead_execution: edit code/docs for bead AC. Only broad queue-steward default is overridden; tracker, merge-policy, verification, safety stay active. Bead description/AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and defaults.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other instruction files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Long-running matrix/benchmark beads\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;For expensive commands (benchmarks, load tests, validation \u0026gt; 60s per variant):\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Write a matrix plan before launching expensive commands: list required configs, output paths, completion criteria.\u0026#xA;- Do not re-run the same long-running command unless: (1) the command fingerprint changed (args/env/config), AND (2) you document why prior output is invalid and what changed.\u0026#xA;- If a long-running command times out or is incomplete, exit with `status: open` + retryable `reason` in `no_changes_rationale.txt`. Do not silently retry; let the orchestrator decide.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-34ea2a74\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003eagent: normalize readiness refinable aliases and diagnose schema drift\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;During the 2026-06-14 dogfood worker restart, readiness for ddx-824079ce returned classification=\u0026#34;refinable\u0026#34; after useful inspection, but DDx rejected it with `unknown classification \u0026#34;refinable\u0026#34;: expected one of ready, needs_refine, needs_split, operator_required, system_unready` and then fail-opened with `readiness check unavailable`. A similar helix readiness pass returned executable prose but surfaced as `system_unready`. DDx/FIZ must make provider/schema drift actionable and must not disguise common near-miss readiness output as project unreadiness.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\u0026#xA;cli/internal/agent/readiness_classification.go:126-140 normalizes several aliases, including actionable_but_rewritten, rewritten, and safely_refinable, but omits the plain `refinable` alias that providers naturally emit. cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:2751-2804 and :2830-2854 convert intake errors into `pre_claim_intake.system_unready` warnings with the generic suggested action `check the readiness route or harness configuration and retry`, losing whether the problem was an output-schema/normalization issue versus a real project readiness blocker.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;- Normalize `classification: \u0026#34;refinable\u0026#34;` to `needs_refine` in the readiness classifier.\u0026#xA;- Add regression coverage proving `refinable` does not become an unknown classification and is handled according to the existing warn/block quality mode.\u0026#xA;- Improve intake-error diagnostics so unknown readiness classifications are recorded as provider/schema drift with the raw classification and accepted enum set, not as generic system_unready project failure.\u0026#xA;- Preserve the existing fail-open behavior unless quality mode says to block; this bead is about correct classification and observability, not making readiness stricter.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;- Do not change the canonical readiness enum names.\u0026#xA;- Do not alter FIZ route selection.\u0026#xA;- Do not change the worker claim/lease policy beyond diagnostics for unknown readiness classification.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. `TestNormalizeReadinessClassificationRefinableAlias` proves `ClassifyReadinessWithMode(\u0026#34;refinable\u0026#34;, ...)` normalizes to `needs_refine` rather than returning an unknown classification.\u0026#xA;2. `TestReadinessUnknownClassificationDiagnosticNamesSchemaDrift` proves an unknown readiness classification records a diagnostic that includes the raw classification and the accepted enum set, and does not describe the bead itself as system-unready without that schema-drift context.\u0026#xA;3. `TestPreClaimIntakeRefinableAliasFollowsNeedsRefinePolicy` proves the work/pre-claim path treats `classification: \u0026#34;refinable\u0026#34;` like `needs_refine` under existing warn/block quality modes.\u0026#xA;4. Existing readiness classification tests in `cli/internal/agent/readiness_schema_test.go` and work readiness tests continue to pass.\u0026#xA;5. `cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/agent/... ./cmd/... -run \u0026#39;TestNormalizeReadinessClassificationRefinableAlias|TestReadinessUnknownClassificationDiagnosticNamesSchemaDrift|TestPreClaimIntakeRefinableAliasFollowsNeedsRefinePolicy\u0026#39; -count=1` passes.\\n6. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ephase:build, area:agent, area:work, kind:bug, kind:reliability, kind:observability, severity:high, provider-supervision, dogfood\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"ddx-9d1af129\" spec-id=\"IP-2026-06-13-server-managed-workers\" base-rev=\"b643687b0d3ba3b82f17d352c509220f0e47f541\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260615T043027-6dad3872\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cref id=\"IP-2026-06-13-server-managed-workers\" path=\"docs/helix/06-iterate/server-managed-workers-plan-2026-06-13.md\"\u003eImplementation Plan: Server-Managed Worker Supervision\u003c/ref\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"DDX_ATTEMPT_ID":"20260615T043027-6dad3872","DDX_BEAD_ID":"ddx-34ea2a74","DDX_MODE":"bead_execution","GIT_CONFIG_GLOBAL":"/Users/erik/Projects/.ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-34ea2a74-20260615T043027-6dad3872/.ddx/executions/20260615T043027-6dad3872/embedded/git-global.cfg","GIT_CONFIG_SYSTEM":"/dev/null","PATH":"/Users/erik/Projects/.ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-34ea2a74-20260615T043027-6dad3872/.ddx/executions/20260615T043027-6dad3872/embedded/git-bin:/home/erik/.local/bin:/home/erik/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/home/erik/.codex/tmp/arg0/codex-arg0Yu4YDA:/usr/local/cuda/bin:/home/erik/.jbang/bin:/home/erik/.opencode/bin:/Users/erik/.antigravity/antigravity/bin:/home/erik/.local/share/mise/shims:/home/erik/.dotfiles/git-subrepo/lib:/Applications/SnowSQL.app/Contents/MacOS:/home/erik/.local/share/coursier/bin:/home/erik/.dotfiles/git-fuzzy/bin:/home/erik/go/bin:/home/erik/.dotfiles/scripts:/home/erik/.cargo/bin:/usr/local/sbin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin:/sbin:/bin:/usr/games:/usr/local/games:/snap/bin:/Users/erik/Library/Application Support/JetBrains/Toolbox/scripts:/Users/erik/Library/Application Support/Coursier/bin:/home/erik/.lmstudio/bin:/home/erik/.cache/lm-studio/bin:/Users/erik/.cache/lm-studio/bin:/Users/erik/.lmstudio/bin","attempt_id":"20260615T043027-6dad3872","base_rev":"b643687b0d3ba3b82f17d352c509220f0e47f541","bead_id":"ddx-34ea2a74","bundle_path":".ddx/executions/20260615T043027-6dad3872","correlation_id":"ddx-34ea2a74:20260615T043027-6dad3872","prompt_file":".ddx/executions/20260615T043027-6dad3872/prompt.md","prompt_sha":"9ce8349eeccee8fdf272642ce51ded9af3fd1f25f7fda72c661775136e785687","role":"implementer","session_id":"eb-539efaea","worker_id":""}}}
